<subSubSection id="7B5B8939D2C90A88B4A4E5FC2875C6E6" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="7D697C3B28D27936AB26F4B75A5F804D" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="14D1400C8A38B2C3F86C466FB2010037" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">
The common widespread species of large 
<taxonomicName id="00EED55945C1C2CDDD864700F380CEB7" authorityName="J.R.Spence" authorityYear="1996" class="Bryopsida" family="Bryaceae" genus="Rosulabryum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Rosulabryum" order="Bryales" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A751B57CB4A1CBF20110509D3ED08A6D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">Rosulabryum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from central Chile south to 
<normalizedToken id="79EAE2BA41D894B5A9D3002C66E6C797" originalValue="Aisén">Aisen</normalizedToken>
. The species is also found in Argentina, the Falkland Islands, Australia, New Zealand and Macquarie Island (
<bibRefCitation id="34D2769944421AE1DD73300D4F911933" DOI="https://doi.org/10.7751/telopea13056" author="Spence, JR" journalOrPublisher="Telopea" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" pagination="99 - 134" refId="B27" refString="Spence, JR, Ramsay, HP, 2019. Revised keys and additions to the Australian Bryaceae (Bryopsida). Telopea 22: 99 - 134, DOI: https://doi.org/10.7751/telopea13056" title="Revised keys and additions to the Australian Bryaceae (Bryopsida)." url="https://doi.org/10.7751/telopea13056" volume="22" year="2019">Spence and Ramsay 2019</bibRefCitation>
). In the Magellanes Region it is largely replaced by 
<taxonomicName id="50AF3290842C1B4A72F04765240A907C" class="Bryopsida" family="Bryaceae" genus="R." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="R. perlimbatum" order="Bryales" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="perlimbatum">
<emphasis id="B39977009DAF79A96A11F207ECBB838C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">R. perlimbatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The species occurs in a variety of forested and semi-open habitats, often in shade on mesic to damp soil banks, fallen logs, tree stumps and soil-covered ledges. It is characterized by dioicous sexual condition, strongly rosulate stems, large leaves that are irregularly contorted when dry, a costa excurrent into a short awn, a strong limbidium, serrate leaf margins, and brown to red-brown rhizoidal tubers (Illustrations: 
<bibRefCitation id="D1B462A3A3D4CA50E07D7D9CDCAD09F3" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1179/jbr.1979.10.4.401" author="Mohamed, MA" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Bryology" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" pagination="401 - 465" refId="B12" refString="Mohamed, MA, 1979. A taxonomic study of Bryum billardieri Schwaegr. and related species. Journal of Bryology 10 (4): 401 - 465, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1179/jbr.1979.10.4.401" title="A taxonomic study of Bryum billardieri Schwaegr. and related species." url="https://doi.org/10.1179/jbr.1979.10.4.401" volume="10" year="1979">Mohamed 1979</bibRefCitation>
: 407, as 
<taxonomicName id="6B09A2482A7BC24502BC324FF77AFE45" class="Bryopsida" family="Bryaceae" genus="Bryum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Bryum billarderii" order="Bryales" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="billarderii">
<emphasis id="CEC6BF9F7F7DD0677CA6A4FE08580682" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">Bryum billarderii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="298DA221F84E5626FCFCEA12C3013E51" author="Spence, JR" editor="McCarthy, PM" journalOrPublisher="CSIRO Press, Canberra" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" pagination="274 - 348" refId="B26" refString="Spence, JR, Ramsay, HP, 2006. Bryaceae. In: McCarthy, PM, Ed., Flora of Australia, Volume 51, Mosses 1. CSIRO Press, Canberra: 274 - 348" title="Bryaceae." volumeTitle="Flora of Australia, Volume 51, Mosses 1." year="2006">Spence and Ramsay 2006</bibRefCitation>
: 335, as 
<taxonomicName id="39CE47466EB403C0327E60A0ADE7CABB" class="Bryopsida" family="Bryaceae" genus="R." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="R. billarderii" order="Bryales" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="billarderii">
<emphasis id="FD87388541983E8710B8D4485B5E9B50" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">R. billarderii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="7B527F89A3C4A9B5115BE881B1D26681" author="Fife, AJ" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" publicationUrl="https://www.nzflora.info/publications.htmlmosses" refId="B4" refString="Fife, AJ, 2015. Flora of New Zealand. Mosses. Fascicle 19, Bryaceae. Lincoln, N.Z., Manaaki Whenua Press (online at: https://www.nzflora.info/publications.htmlmosses" title="Flora of New Zealand. Mosses. Fascicle 19, Bryaceae. Lincoln, N. Z., Manaaki Whenua Press (online at:" url="https://www.nzflora.info/publications.htmlmosses" year="2015">Fife 2015</bibRefCitation>
: 84, as 
<taxonomicName id="B45D42137048EE2AAB3B389A0762223C" class="Bryopsida" family="Bryaceae" genus="R." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="R. billarderii" order="Bryales" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="billarderii">
<emphasis id="28B596601F95F1B864E36A964CEB2754" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">R. billarderii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
